---
title: Labyrinth | Shakeel Mohamed — Strategic Brand Designer
description: Strategic brand designer in Los Angeles specializing in identity design, typography, and systems thinking. Available for freelance and full-time opportunities.
---

extends ../_includes/layouts/base.pug

block content
    .grid-1
        h1 Welcome to my Labyrinth
        //- TODO: another cool feature could be like soot.world, allow for different/random animated viewing of images when clicking on these icons
        .flex.justify-between.labyrinth-icons
            span.material-icons swap_calls
            span.material-icons zoom_out_map
            span.material-icons cached
            span.material-icons recycling
    .grid-2
        div
            p Design, like a labyrinth, is not about rushing to the end but discovery along the way. Unlike a maze, which focuses on solving and escaping, a labyrinth invites mindful exploration. The winding path of creativity reflects the cyclical nature of design. Each project offers new ideas and insights building upon the last.
        div
            p This is my home for archived, unpolished, philosophical creative exploration.
            br
            p You can drag these items around, have fun!

    .grid-1.full-width
        .labyrinth(id="labyrinth")
            .image-gallery.preserve-3d(image-gallery="smgallery" image-gallery-row="")
                .thumbnail_sizer

    script(type="application/json" id="labyrinth-images-data")!= JSON.stringify(labyrinth)
    script(src="../scripts/gsap/gsap.min.js" type="text/javascript")
    script(src="../scripts/gsap/Draggable.min.js" type="text/javascript")
    script(src="../scripts/labyrinth.js" type="text/javascript")
    <style> #labyrinth-copy { position: fixed; bottom: 16px; right: 16px; z-index: 9999; padding: 8px 12px; background: #000000; color: #ffffff; border: none; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; }</style>
